  "text": "Seismic models perpendicular to island arcs show similar velocity structure in the arc itself with velocities ranging from ca. 2 to 7.5 km/ s, whereas velocities are smaller than 6.7 km/s in the backarc region of the Kuril Arc (Fig. 3) , and up-to 6.9 km/s in the Aleutian arc. In the Aleutian arc, there is some evidence from ringing reflectivity, that the underplating may be taking place in the form of sill intrusions into the lower crust at the back-arc side of the system [CITATION_1] ).",
